Wishing Wands
Artist: Wowhause
2009

Wishing Wands
evoke the childhood tradition of making a wish by blowing on a dandelion
seed head. These interactive sculptures are designed to be accessible
to children of all physical capabilities: each seed head features 38 2
1/2"" Austrian Crystals that catch the light, refracting sunlight in
prismatic rainbows children can "catch" and play in. The three
sculptures are sited near an accessible playground in a public park.
Schoolchildren participated in making wishes on each of the crystals
before they were incorporated into the sculptures. 


    
        
             District
            4
            
        
        
