We Live Here
Artist: Ries Niemi
2004

We Live Here
is a community-generated public art project located at the Alma/Almaden
median. This stainless steel open frame column was created by artist
Ries Niemi. The base of the column is layered with images of
the indigenous topography and local architectural elements found
throughout the neighborhood. Wrapping around the layers is a simple
declarative statement, “We
Live Here” in the Ohlone, English and Spanish languages. 



    
        
