Veterans Memorial of San José ~ Santa Clara Valley
Artist Team: Manhattan Projects
1997

Located on Park Avenue at the Guadalupe River, the Veterans Memorial is an enduring tribute to the men and women who have served our country in peacetime and in times of war. The artwork is comprised of 76 white flags on stainless steel poles in formation beyond a wall of glass imprinted with photos of local soldiers and communications sent back home during times of service; the threshold in front of the glass is inlaid with military insignias. 



    
        
