Artist: Michael Boris
1991
A set of bronze animals represents creatures that might be found along the Guadalupe River. The animals are arranged so that the owl, hawk, and fox are eyeing the rabbit and frog as food sources. The raccoon is placed as an observer, watching all the other animals.



    
        
