Los Viajeros Vienen a San Jose
Artist: Maria Alguilar
1991
 The work is a story of two travelers on a yellow horse visiting San Jose. The rest of the mural illustrates different venues, most particularly the Freedom Train. The travelers departing from the Freedom Train illustrate the vast ethnic groups that live in the City.In 2010, this work was moved from its original location at the San Jose International Airport to installed at the Biblioteca Latinoamericana Branch Library.



    
        
