La Vida en Dichos
Artist: Pilar Aguero

2009

Five murals composed of numerous panels of various sizes, put
together like a puzzle. The themes of each mural relate to San Jose: the land and
valley; education; heroes and history; love and art; and ancestors, legacy and
future. Images are woven together thematically by Spanish dichos, popular
Spanish proverbs and sayings that communicate simple wisdom. The dichos
are translated into English through 3-dimensional text mounted on the adjacent
walls.



    
        
