Hand in Hand
Artist: Michael Stutz
2005The work depicts a small hand in the middle of a large hand, suggesting relationship between adult and child, large and small.  Located atop of a small mound at the entryway into the community center and adjacent to the playing fields, it serves to greet people as they come to the facility. Viewers regularly see children waving at the artwork from cars as they enter the community facility.




    
        
